{"title_page": "Namaiki Zakari", "text_new": "{{short description|Shojo manga series}}\n{{Use mdy dates|date=July 2019}}\n{{Infobox animanga/Header\n| name            = Namaiki Zakari\n| image           = Namaiki Zakari.jpg\n| image_size      = \n| caption         = Cover of the first volume\n| ja_kanji        = \u306a\u307e\u3044\u304d\u3056\u304b\u308a\u3002\n| ja_romaji       = \n| genre           = <!-- Note: Use and cite reliable sources to identify genre/s, not personal interpretation. Please don't include more than three genres (per [[MOS:A&M]]). -->\n}}\n{{Infobox animanga/Print\n| type            = manga\n| author          = Mitsubachi Miyuki\n| publisher       = [[Hakusensha]]\n| publisher_en    = \n| demographic     = ''[[Sh\u014djo manga|Sh\u014djo]]''\n| magazine        = [[Hana to Yume]]\n| imprint         = Hana to Yume Comics\n| first           = November 2013\n| last            = \n| volumes         = 17\n| volume_list     = \n}}\n{{Infobox animanga/Footer}}\n\n{{nihongo|'''''Namaiki Zakari'''''|\u306a\u307e\u3044\u304d\u3056\u304b\u308a\u3002||{{literal translation|lk=yes}} \"Full Bloom Cheekiness\"|lead=yes}} is a Japanese ''[[sh\u014djo manga|sh\u014djo]]'' [[manga]] series by Mitsubachi Miyuki. It has been [[serial (literature)|serialized]] in the semi-monthly [[List of manga magazines|manga magazine]] ''[[Hana to Yume]]'' since November 2013. During the series' run, a drama CD was released with the 10th volume.<ref name=\"drama cd\">{{cite news|url=https://natalie.mu/comic/news/154196|title=\u300c\u306a\u307e\u3044\u304d\u3056\u304b\u308a\u3002\u300d\u30c9\u30e9\u30deCD\u5316\uff01\u5357\u689d\u611b\u4e43\u3001\u4f50\u85e4\u62d3\u4e5f\u3001\u5c0f\u91ce\u53cb\u6a39\u304c\u51fa\u6f14|language=ja|work=[[Natalie (website)|Natalie]]|date=2015-07-17|accessdate=2018-10-24}}</ref> A live-action short movie was released on [[Hakusensha]]'s official [[YouTube]] channel to promote the release of the 12th volume.<ref name=\"short movie\">{{cite news|url=https://natalie.mu/comic/news/270216|title=\u300c\u306a\u307e\u3044\u304d\u3056\u304b\u308a\u3002\u300d\u5b9f\u5199\u30b7\u30e7\u30fc\u30c8\u30e0\u30fc\u30d3\u30fc\u3001\u6c34\u8c37\u679c\u7a42\uff06\u4e95\u962a\u90c1\u5df3\u304c\u30de\u30f3\u30ac\u3092\u518d\u73fe|language=ja|work=[[Natalie (website)|Natalie]]|date=2018-02-20|accessdate=2018-10-24}}</ref>\n\n==Plot==\nYuki Machida, a second-year high school student, is the manager of the school's basketball team and has spent her childhood masking her emotions after years of caring for her five siblings as the eldest. During the welcoming ceremony, she meets Sho Naruse, an impudent student a year her junior who also joins the basketball team. Day after day, Sho tests her patience with his selfish and lecherous comments. However, Yuki is in love with the basketball team's captain, Kido, who had recently gotten a girlfriend. One day, Sho finds out Yuki's feelings for Kido, to her dismay, but he supports her during times of distress. After the final match of the year, Sho admits to Yuki that he is in love with her and declares to win her over.\n\n==Characters==\n===Main characters===\n;{{nihongo|Yuki Machida|\u753a\u7530 \u7531\u5e0c|Machida Yuki}}\n:{{Voiced by|[[Yoshino Nanj\u014d]]}} (drama CD);<ref name=\"drama cd\"/> Kaho Mizutani (short movie)<ref name=\"short movie\"/>\n:Yuki is a beautiful second-year high school student and the manager of the basketball team. She is cool-headed and masks her emotions, traits she learned from taking care of her five younger siblings since youth, but she becomes flustered when it comes to Sho. The basketball team values her for being diligent and organized.\n;{{nihongo|Sho Naruse|\u6210\u702c \u7fd4|Naruse Sh\u014d}}\n:{{Voiced by|[[Takuya Sat\u014d (voice actor)|Takuya Sato]]}} (drama CD);<ref name=\"drama cd\"/> Ikumi Isaka (short movie)<ref name=\"short movie\"/>\n:Sho is a first-year high school student and a member of the basketball team. He instantly falls for Yuki despite his popularity with the girls, and though his immaturity clashes with her more responsible habits, he becomes persistent in winning her over.\n\n===Ryuhoku High School===\n;{{nihongo|Kido|\u6728\u6238}}\n:Kido is a third-year high school student and is the captain of the basketball team. Yuki at first has feelings for him, but he and Rina begin dating. He graduates after the final match of the year and starts attending university.\n;{{nihongo|Rina Hashino|\u6a4b\u91ce \u30ea\u30ca|Hashino Rina}}\n:Rina is a third-year-high school student and Kido's bubbly girlfriend.\n;{{nihongo|Arisa Ichii|\u5e02\u4e95 \u3042\u308a\u3055|Ichii Arisa}}\n:Arisa is a close friend of Sho's and attended the same junior high school. She has a strong personality and speaks her mind. She has been in love with Sho for a long time, but she later comes to accept his feelings for Yuki.\n\n===Misuzu Academy===\n;{{nihongo|Shizuka Hakamada|\u88b4\u7530 \u9759|Hakamada Shizuka}}\n:{{voiced by|[[Yuuki Ono]]}} (drama CD)<ref name=\"drama cd\"/>\n:Shizuka is Sho's childhood friend and had attended the same elementary school before relocating to Kyushu. He considers Sho his rival and is motivated to perform well at basketball to defeat him. Though Shizuka has trouble talking to women, he becomes attracted to Yuki and falls in love with her. After graduating Misuzu Academy, he attends the same college as Yuki and Sho, playing on the same basketball team.\n\n===College===\n;{{nihongo|Suwa|\u8acf\u8a2a|}}\n:Suwa is a member of the college basketball team and works at the same convenience store as Yuki when she starts attending college. He has a reputation of a playboy and is seen with a different girl constantly; however, he becomes fascinated when Yuki shows no interest in him. He falls in love with her, but he later discovers he is mistaking his feelings for the lack of motherly affection in his own childhood after he became estranged from his mother. Suwa later becomes attracted to Usami when she sees him for his true self.\n;{{nihongo|Fuka Usami|\u5b87\u4f50\u898b\u3000\u98a8\u9999|Usami F\u016bka}}\n:Usami is Yuki's next-door neighbor who attends the same college. She is in love with Suwa and downplays his advances, believing him still to be in love with Yuki.\n\n==Media==\n===Manga===\n\n''Namaiki Zakari'' is written and illustrated by Mitsubachi Miyuki. It is serialized in the bimonthly magazine ''[[Hana to Yume]]'' since September 2013. The chapters were later released in [[Tank\u014dbon|bound volumes]] by [[Hakusensha]] under the Hana to Yume Comics imprint. During the series' run, a drama CD was released in limited edition bundle of volume 10.<ref name=\"drama cd\"/>\n\n{{Graphic novel list/header\n| Language        = Japanese\n| OneLanguage     = yes\n}}\n{{Graphic novel list\n| VolumeNumber    = 1\n| OriginalRelDate = May 20, 2014<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.s-book.net/plsql/slib_detail?isbn=9784592213314|title=\u306a\u307e\u3044\u304d\u3056\u304b\u308a\u3002 1|language=ja|work=[[Hakusensha]]|accessdate=2018-10-25}}</ref>\n| OriginalISBN    = 978-4-592-21331-4\n| ChapterList     = \n| Summary         = \n}}\n{{Graphic novel list\n| VolumeNumber    = 2\n| OriginalRelDate = August 20, 2014<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.s-book.net/plsql/slib_detail?isbn=9784592213321|title=\u306a\u307e\u3044\u304d\u3056\u304b\u308a\u3002 2|language=ja|work=[[Hakusensha]]|accessdate=2018-10-25}}</ref>\n| OriginalISBN    = 978-4-592-21332-1\n| ChapterList     = \n| Summary         = \n}}\n{{Graphic novel list\n| VolumeNumber    = 3\n| OriginalRelDate = December 19, 2014<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.s-book.net/plsql/slib_detail?isbn=9784592213338|title=\u306a\u307e\u3044\u304d\u3056\u304b\u308a\u3002 3|language=ja|work=[[Hakusensha]]|accessdate=2018-10-25}}</ref>\n| OriginalISBN    = 978-4-592-21333-8\n| ChapterList     = \n| Summary         = \n}}\n{{Graphic novel list\n| VolumeNumber    = 4\n| OriginalRelDate = May 20, 2015<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.s-book.net/plsql